<paragraph blockId="22.[138,1185,984,1330]" pageId="22" pageNumber="465">
Although we do not consider it to be impossible that an Atlantic species, like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergendal" authorityYear="1890" box="[1056,1177,1178,1202]" family="Uteriporidae" genus="Uteriporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="22" pageNumber="465" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis box="[1056,1177,1178,1202]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="465">U. vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also occurs on the coasts of the Bering Sea, we do here attribute Poljakova’s animals to the species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="? Sluys" authorityYear="1989" box="[228,358,1242,1266]" family="Uteriporidae" genus="Uteriporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="22" pageNumber="465" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="pacificus">
<emphasis box="[228,358,1242,1266]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="465">U. pacificus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, albeit with some reservations in view of the absence of more detailed anatomical information. This record considerably extends the range of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="? Sluys" authorityYear="1989" box="[950,1078,1274,1298]" family="Uteriporidae" genus="Uteriporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="22" pageNumber="465" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="pacificus">
<emphasis box="[950,1078,1274,1298]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="465">U. pacificus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
since the species was originally recorded for the coast of 
<collectingRegion box="[693,898,1306,1330]" country="Canada" name="British Columbia" pageId="22" pageNumber="465">British Columbia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[911,1000,1306,1330]" name="Canada" pageId="22" pageNumber="465">Canada</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sluys R" box="[1017,1154,1306,1330]" pageId="22" pageNumber="465" refId="ref9110" refString="Sluys R. 1989. A Monograph of the Marine Triclads. Rotterdam and Brookfield: A. A. Balkema. XII + 463 p." type="book" year="1989">Sluys 1989</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
